es these essential vitamins it is also rich in minerals such as calcium potassium phosphorus magnesium copper zinc and selenium comfrey roots and leaves are said to provide nutritive healing properties for all different types of ailments because of its high allantoin along with other substances that reduce inflammation and keep skin healthyhorsetail extract   equisetum arvenseit probably got its name due to its likeness to a horses tail in fact the origin of its latin name equisetum a combination of equs meaning horse and seta meaning bristle could be attributed to this resemblance this relative of the fern is a descendant of large plants that grew on earth some  million years ago silica in horsetail extract is thought not only to slow down hair loss in both men and women but also encourages growth of new hair follicles horsetail extract helps to increase blood circulation nourishes hair follicles and assist hair growth the amino acids and phytosterols in horsetail help strengthen hair follicles while also reducing oil buildup on the scalpguava leaf extract   psidium guajavaguava leaves has been traditionally used throughout history by many folk cultures it can be used on damaged skin acne skin inflammations irritation and itching it is beneficial for fading blemishes and clearing dandruff this leaf can be used on skin scalp and hair these leaves contain a number of beneficial substances including antioxidants like vitamins a c b k beta carotene iron calcium potassium phosphorus and flavonoids such as quercetin guava leaves contain powerful antibacterial compounds that work well for skin and scalp infections it may help with inflammation and itching from dandruffbanaba extract   lagerstroemia speciosabanaba is a species of crepe myrtle tree that is native to southeast asia it is believed that the leaves of banaba have therapeutic properties banaba leaf extract contains a compound known as corosolic acid which is reputed for topical use to reduce lipid content of skinnettle root extract   urtica dioicanettle root has been used since ancient times as a hair treatment growth stimulant and to help restore nutritive hair color and shine it is said that the ancient greeks romans and the native tribes of america had used this herb for medicinal purposes the root contains polysaccharides and lignans that have an effect similar to steroid hormones it may that may possess antiviral properties and acts as an antiinflammatory  plantain extract  plantago majornative americans carried powdered roots of plantain as protection against snake bites the herb has a long history of use as an alternative medicine dating back to ancient times plantain contains allantoin which is an antiinflammatory that kills germs helps healing and stimulates the growth of new skin cells thus benefiting your scalp and folliclesburdock root extract   arctium lappait is popularly known as oriental ginseng in japan the plant has large leaves and purple flowers resembling thistle flowers the root of the plant is used for cosmetic and medicinal purposes including promoting healthy hair burdock makes hair healthy by improving scalp circulation it improves the strength and helps with hair loss burdock root is a very nutritious it contains a high amount of vitamins a c b e and kapple cider vinegar   malus domesticaapple cider vinegar contains the mother of vinegar and is made using only the best freshlypressed apples the apple cider vinegar is raw unfiltered and unpasteurized preserving the fragile essential nutrients it can inhibit bacteria mold and germs yet it is environmentally safe apple cider vinegar has been highly regarded throughout history in  bc the great hippocrates father of medicine used it for its amazing health qualities it contains valuable enzymes botanical acids and vitamins its nutritive acidity discourages buildup on the scalp and adjusts skin ph when applied topically the acidity of apple cider vinegar changes the ph of your scalp so it’s not an ideal environment for yeast that can cause dandruff to grow vinegar has been used for decades to help with dandruffaloe vera   aloe barbadensisaloe vera has been used for improving skin conditions as the ancient egyptians called it the “plant of immortality” a succulent plant with rejuvenating and soothing properties aloe vera holds many benefits for the skin it has been used topically for thousands of years to improve skin conditions it contains vitamins a c e b b b b and b aloe vera also contains over  other naturally occurring nutrients such as enzymes amino acids and sterols aloe gel is extracted from the leaves of the plant and when applied to the skin softens dead skin cells leaving the skin feeling soft and smooth                                               testimonials               customer hair products reviews and testimonials are provided for informational purposes only customer hair products reviews and testimonials reflect the individual hair products reviewer’s results and experiences only hair products results may vary based on individual user                   this is a great nutritive product i noticed the difference in my hair after using it only once leaves my hair soft and really clean scalp removing product buildup its great to have as an alternate shampoo doesnt leave my hair dry highly recommendedsallie l westport ctthe water in my apartment building is extremely harsh and drying to my relaxed color treated hair no matter what moisturizing shampoo i used my hair never felt as soft as it did leaving my hair salon i was told mineral deposits in water will cause hair to dry and eventually break i bought this and i am hooked my hair felt so soft and manageable i only use this product once a month it has greatly improved my hair conditionjamie s sarasota flthis vinegar rinse to remove build up is awesome i have very fine limp hair this adds volume and shine while removing all the buildup from styling products and it smells great too i love it and wou